threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a Mirai-like IoT botnet worm. It contains a large, hardcoded list of default credentials in the function `sub_410c08` (e.g., `root:vizxv`, `admin:admin`, `support:support`) used to brute-force other devices. The malware also includes downloader functionality, using commands like `wget`, `tftp`, `ftpget`, and `curl` to fetch and execute secondary payloads from a command-and-control server. Strings such as `GET /dlr.` and `/wget.sh -O- | sh` confirm its role as a downloader and dropper.
